class Solution {
public:
    string answerString(string word, int numFriends) {
        sort(word.begin(), word.end(), greater<char>());
        return word.substr(0, 1 + (word.size() - 1) / numFriends);
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n log n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The approach leverages sorting the characters in the string in descending order, then determining the lexicographically largest string by taking a substring that ensures the string can be split into `numFriends` non-empty parts without repeating any split. This method efficiently achieves the goal by minimizing the number of operations required.

